  <summary date="2019-02-14T05:00:00Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Korematsu-Takai Civil Liberties Protection Act of 2019

This bill modifies the detention authority of the United States.

Specifically, it prohibits detention or imprisonment based solely on an actual or perceived protected characteristic of an individual. A protected characteristic includes each of the following: race, ethnicity, national origin, religion, sex, gender identity, sexual orientation, disability, and any additional characteristic that the Department of Justice determines to be a protected characteristic.</summary>
